The Country Director of Rise Up, an international charity, Theresa Effa, has advised non-governmental organisations in the country to increase efforts towards acquiring advocacy and leadership skills. She made the call in Abuja during a workshop organized by Rise Up to strengthen the capacity of 24 NGOs drawn from Nasarawa and Kaduna states. Matan arewa present excellence award to Daily Trust Foundation Consensus: Buhari didn’t order fee refunds to aspirants – Akume She said doing so would enable them effectively advocate for women and girls issues and get policy and decision-makers to address challenges confronting women and girls. Dr Onawale Aboki, a consultant to the project, said most NGOs lack basic skills in advocacy.